cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the interpretation of propositional dynamic logic (PDL) through Kripke models and discusses the expressivity of probabilistic models for PDL.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as PDL is commonly used in AI for reasoning about actions and change.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the interpretation of programs in PDL.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses rewrite rules for building up an interpretation of PDL.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the properties of bisimilarity and relates them to a closely related non-dynamic logic of the Hennessy-Milner type.
